parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls
especially when parallel parking or parking on slopes
the vehicle fails to start
and there is a noxious smell inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage and potentially causing a fire.
symptoms: The temperature gauge shows the vehicle is overheating
the engine stalls
and there is white thick smoke coming from under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The check engine light stays on
the vehicle stalls
and there is a problem with the wiring harness.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
especially when shifting gears
and there is a problem with the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine fails
especially when accelerating
and there is a problem with the engine head gasket.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical wiring harness can cause a range of issues, including engine failure, electrical fires, and loss of critical vehicle systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the vehicle loses power
the electrical system malfunctions
the wiring harness is damaged or corroded
the insulation on the wires is flaking off
and there are signs of electrical fires or burning smells.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blower motor can cause reduced visibility due to fog or frost, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The blower motor fails to work
the defroster and heater do not function
and there is reduced visibility due to fog or frost.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Instrument Panel and Tail Light Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel and tail lights can cause reduced visibility, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The instrument panel lights and tail lights do not function
and there is reduced visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shifts erratically
hesitates
or slips
the transmission indicator light comes on
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission fails to engage into gear
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PRNDL indicator can cause the driver to be unaware of the gear selection, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The PRNDL indicator is broken
the shift lever does not indicate the correct gear
the shift lever hangs up when switching between gears
the driver is unable to determine the gear selection.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the transmission to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The torque converter fails
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission indicator light comes on.
